_label: Wearing a variety of t-shirts with portraits of Che Guevara and Salvador Allende, these young communists participate in a party rally in Oviedo, Northern Spain. It was the last weekend for the five major political parties during their electoral campaign prior to the nation's voting on the 15th of June. Throughout the country in football fields and bullrings, in town halls and cinemas, the various leaders made their last efforts for the country's first free election in 41 years. The latest polls show that Prime Minister Adolfo Suarez's party, the "Democratic Center Union," emerges as perhaps the strongest group, but without a working majority, they may be forced to form a coalition with the Socialists
